occur until 1944-1945.<br>
<br>
Daylight raids by the 8th airforce were a failure until long range<br>
fighter escorts (P-51 Mustang) were able to protect the bombers<br>
for their entire mission.  Before that happened, the German<br>
Luftwaffe inflicted so serious casualties that the US Army<br>
had considered putting a halt to all daylight raids.<br>
<br>
In this alternate version question, What if the Germans had <br>
won WWII? I'm not looking for the obvious response, which is<br>
'But they didn't win!'  What I'm looking for is what would the<br>
world be like today as a result?  Would the Germans continued<br>
on with more advanced rocketry?  Would most of civilization<br>
be destroyed in a nuclear WWIII? etc.<br>
